reviewText: When I first saw this movie I thought it was made in 2013 it is not, it was made in 1986 but put on dvd in 2013, being filmed in 1986 it does have that stage look that most movies produced by the BBC had in the 80's (think "Chronicles of Narnia).This dvd is a musical and despite being blue on the cover Alice's dress and headband are pink.I am planning on getting the sequel"Through the looking glass"

Title: Alice in Wonderland

reviewText: Shipping was fast and movie was in great condition. Just not what I thought the movie would be. And it's not the seller's fault obviously. I was hoping for more especially from BBC productions, but with so many Alice versions out there, you can't like them all I guess.
Title: Alice in Wonderland

reviewText: I really enjoyed this version of Alice in Wonderland. It followed the actual story almost perfectly, unlike most versions. The costuming was really quite beautiful. The whole miniseries was done in almost a story book appearance. Through the entire show, the background appears to be done with a green screen, which the story book looking background was later added. I personally liked the look of it, because it gave you the feeling of being inside the story. I not only recommend this version to collectors like myself, but I also recommend it to anyone who would like to experience Alice in Wonderland, other than the well known Disney version.
Title: Alice in Wonderland
